message.content:
cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.Distributed, cs.HPC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a frequent item problem and presents a shared-memory version of the Space Saving algorithm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses parallel shared-memory algorithms and investigates a hybrid MPI/OpenMP version against a pure MPI based version. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper studies the behavior of the algorithm with regard to accuracy and performance on many and multi-core processors, including the Intel Phi accelerator. 
- cs.Distributed is relevant as the paper deals with parallel algorithms and discusses a hybrid MPI/OpenMP version. 
- cs.HPC (High Performance Computing) is also relevant as the paper investigates the performance of the algorithm on many and multi-core processors, including the Intel Phi accelerator.
